<emphasis bold="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
Three 
<typeStatus box="[199,356,949,971]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
, two males and one female, with the following labels: first male with two labels, one printed “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1360,1436,949,971]" name="Bolivia" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
Coroico (
<quantity box="[294,367,980,1002]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" unit="m" value="1400.0">1400m</quantity>
) (Fassl)” and a handwritten 
<typeStatus box="[656,700,981,1002]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">type</typeStatus>
label; second male with three labels: two identical to the other male and one handwritten label in blue ink “ 
<taxonomicName box="[549,652,1010,1032]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pompiliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acroleuca">acroleuca</taxonomicName>
”; female with labels as for the first male 
<typeStatus box="[1067,1207,1010,1032]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">paralectotype</typeStatus>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1077,1282]" box="[151,844,1077,1102]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,412,1077,1102]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Current combination.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zerny, 1931" authorityName="Zerny" authorityYear="1931" box="[419,841,1077,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Sphecosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acroleuca">
<emphasis box="[419,677,1077,1102]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Sphecosoma acroleuca</emphasis>
(Zerny, 
<number box="[772,832,1078,1102]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" value="1931.0">1931</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1077,1282]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,605,1113,1138]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
Condition of the 
<typeStatus box="[402,466,1113,1138]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">types</typeStatus>
. 
<typeStatus box="[479,599,1113,1138]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Left antenna missing. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,1046,1113,1138]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
<typeStatus box="[863,1041,1113,1138]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Paralectotypes</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
First male with forewings slightly damaged. Second male with worn wings and left antenna broken. Female with apex of left forewing missing and slight damage to the right forewing and left hindwing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="517" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1077,1282]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1221,1246]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from the four specimens found at the 
<collectionCode box="[1094,1187,1222,1245]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/91g3-0mnw" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">NHMW</collectionCode>
. It was transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1876" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1876" box="[151,435,1257,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Sphecosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,291,1257,1282]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Sphecosoma</emphasis>
Butler, 
<number box="[379,435,1257,1282]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" value="1876.0">1876</number>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[477,793,1257,1282]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" refString="Simmons, R. B. &amp; Weller, S. J. (2006) Review of the Sphecosoma genus group using adult morphology (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Thomas Say Publications in Entomology: Monographs. Published by the Entomological Society of America, Lanham, Maryland, 108 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Simmons and Weller (
<number box="[724,785,1257,1282]" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who assigned it to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1053,1270,1257,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Sphecosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="517" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aliena">
<emphasis box="[1053,1270,1257,1282]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="517">Sphecosoma aliena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
